    "body": "## Problem\n\n\n## Steps to reproduce\nsource this script\n```lua\nvim.defer_fn(vim.cmd.startinsert, 50)\nvim.defer_fn(vim.cmd.stopinsert, 100)\nvim.defer_fn(vim.cmd.startinsert, 100)\n```\n\n## Expected behavior\nI'm not sure if this a bug, I found this when debugging some other thing. \nI Expect it to be in insert mode. But it's normal mode.\n\n## System info\n\n- Nvim version (nvim -v): `v0.13.0-dev-254 g310cc36fda` neovim/neovim@310cc36fda\n- Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?: ?\n- Operating system/version: Linux 6.19.11-zen1-1-zen\n- Terminal name/version: kitty\n- $TERM environment variable: `xterm-kitty`\n- Installation: ?\n\n",
